org.jcvi.jillion.core.io

Interface InputStreamSupplier

  • Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface InputStreamSupplier
    A Supplier function that can create multiple new InputStreams from the same source file. Different implementations may be able to handle different file encodings or compressions.
    Author:
    dkatzel
    Since:
    5.0

      • get

        default InputStream get(long startOffset)
                 throws IOException
        Create a new InputStream that starts at the specified byte start offset.
        Implementation Note:
        the default implementation creates a new InputStream via get() and then skips over startOffset number of bytes. Implementations should override this method if they are able to more efficiently start in the middle of an InputStream.
        Parameters:
        startOffset - the number of uncompressed bytes to skip over before returning the InputStream.
        Returns:
        a new InputStream; should never be null but might not have any bytes to read.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem creating the InputStream or skipping over the desired number of bytes.

      • forFile

        static InputStreamSupplier forFile(File f)
                            throws IOException
        Create a new InputStreamSupplier for the given File and try to correctly automatically decompress it. The first few bytes of the given file are parsed to see if it is one of the few compressed file formats that have built-in JDK InputStream implementations. Currently the only supported formats are:
        • uncompressed
        • zip - single entry only
        • gzip
        If the file is not one of these types, then it is assumed to be uncompressed and an InputStreamSupplier implementation based on FileInputStream will be returned. File encoding is determined by the actual contents of the file. The file name is not examined at all so input files may use any file name extension conventions without worrying about this method misinterpreting.
        Parameters:
        f - the File object to create an InputStreamSupplier for; can not be null, must exist,must be readable and should continue to exist for the lifetime of this InputStreamSupplier.
        Returns:
        a new InputStreamSupplier; will never be null.
        Throws:
        IOException - if there is a problem reading this file.
        NullPointerException - if f is null.
